theorem
(((a <> ( 0 ) & m <> ( 0 )) & a,m are_relative_prime ) implies (for b holds ( a |^ b ),m are_relative_prime ))
proof
defpred P[ Nat ]
 means
( a |^ $1 ),m are_relative_prime ;
assume A1: ((a <> ( 0 ) & m <> ( 0 )) & a,m are_relative_prime );
A2: (for b holds (P[ b ] implies P[ ( b + 1 ) ]))
proof
let b;
A3: ( a |^ ( b + 1 ) ) = ( ( a |^ b ) * ( a |^ 1 ) ) by NEWTON:8
.= ( ( a |^ b ) * a ) by NEWTON:5;
